<subSubSection id="50C98CD9FFBDB328FF1C790BCF26F84F" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="186CDF52FFBDB328FF1C790BCF26F84F" blockId="2.[151,1436,1554,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FF1C790BCC5FF9F6" bold="true" box="[151,330,1554,1581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">New diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body mid-sized (
<quantity id="DF2B72B7FFBDB328FD9F790BCF85F9F7" box="[532,656,1555,1581]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" unit="mm" value="35.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="30.0">30–40 mm</quantity>
) and robust, the only known species reddish-brown (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FB62790BC822F9F7" box="[1257,1335,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,201,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[162,1426,181,1935]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Male habitus. A. Lateral, B. Dorsal, and C. Frontal views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453429/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FACD790BC842F9F7" box="[1350,1367,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[191,1416,213,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-28@7.[151,1436,181,1818]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Female habitus. A. Lateral, B. Dorsal, and C. Frontal views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453435/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">4</figureCitation>
). Pronotum very granulated, with lateral lobes projecting laterally in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FB8A792FC971F98B" box="[1025,1124,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,201,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[162,1426,181,1935]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Male habitus. A. Lateral, B. Dorsal, and C. Frontal views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453429/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Figs. 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FBF9792FC983F98B" box="[1138,1174,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[191,1416,213,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-28@7.[151,1436,181,1818]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Female habitus. A. Lateral, B. Dorsal, and C. Frontal views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453435/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">4B</figureCitation>
); meso- and metazonal groove deep and joining at the lateral lobes, forming a delimited region from the rest of the pronotum (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FAB97943CDACF943" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,201,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[162,1426,181,1935]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Male habitus. A. Lateral, B. Dorsal, and C. Frontal views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453429/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Figs. 1A, 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FF4C7967CC09F943" box="[199,284,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[191,1416,213,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-28@7.[151,1436,181,1818]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Female habitus. A. Lateral, B. Dorsal, and C. Frontal views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453435/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">4A, 4B</figureCitation>
). Brachypterous, wings not covering the last two or three abdominal segments in males (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FA807967C877F943" box="[1291,1378,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,201,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[162,1426,181,1935]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Male habitus. A. Lateral, B. Dorsal, and C. Frontal views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453429/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) and the last four in females (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FE2179BBCF10F967" box="[426,517,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1842,1866]" captionTargetBox="[191,1416,213,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-28@7.[151,1436,181,1818]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Female habitus. A. Lateral, B. Dorsal, and C. Frontal views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453435/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Legs slender and moderately elongated, conspicuously ridged on both outer and inner sides, all femora dorsally unarmed and only the hind tibia bears dorsal spines; fore coxae armed with a conspicuous dorsal spine, ventrally with two tubercles, one at the middle and other at the apex; mid and hind coxae unarmed. Sternum typical of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBDB328FDC17817CFCEF8F3" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[586,731,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platyphyllini">Platyphyllini</taxonomicName>
regarding the organization of furrows. Tenth tergite, epiproct, and male cerci without conspicuous projections nor ornaments (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FCE0782BC916F897" box="[875,1027,1843,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[198,1384,208,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Stridulatory apparatus in dorsal view of A. Left-wing and B. Right-wing. C. Left stridulatory file. Male terminalia in D. Dorsal, E. Ventral, F. Lateral, and G. Axial views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453431/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Figs. 2D, 2G</figureCitation>
). Styli notably elongated, as long as the subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FE0D784FCF02F8AB" box="[390,535,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[198,1384,208,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Stridulatory apparatus in dorsal view of A. Left-wing and B. Right-wing. C. Left stridulatory file. Male terminalia in D. Dorsal, E. Ventral, F. Lateral, and G. Axial views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453431/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Figs. 2E, 2F</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor robust, slightly longer than the hind femur (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FB28784FC82FF8AB" box="[1187,1338,1878,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[180,1391,202,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[151,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Female terminalia in A. Dorsal, B. Lateral, and C. Ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453437/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Figs. 5A, 5B</figureCitation>
), female subgenital plate undivided (
<figureCitation id="80E8C3D7FFBDB328FE457863CF32F84F" box="[462,551,1914,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[180,1391,202,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[151,1436,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Brachyauchenus castaneus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895. Female terminalia in A. Dorsal, B. Lateral, and C. Ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453437/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="50C98CD9FFBDB329FF4C7887CF87FDE6" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="549" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="186CDF52FFBDB328FF4C7887C820F807" blockId="2.[151,1436,1554,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FF4C7887CC73F862" bold="true" box="[199,358,1950,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">
<typeStatus id="C76861F0FFBDB328FF4C7887CC17F863" box="[199,258,1951,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBDB328FEF97887C907F863" authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[370,1042,1950,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FEF97887CFB0F862" box="[370,677,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Brachyauchenus castaneus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBDB328FD3A7887C907F863" author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[689,1042,1950,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" refId="ref7271" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1895) Monographie der Pseudophylliden. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien. 45, 282 pp." type="book" year="1895">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Herein, the genus is regarded as monotypic. The other species that until now were included in this genus are being moved to other genera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="186CDF52FFBCB329FF4C7F8ECF87FDE6" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FF4C7F8ECC77FF6A" bold="true" box="[199,354,150,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Comparison.</emphasis>
In Beier’s key (1960), 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FDE27F8ECE31FF6A" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[617,804,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FDE27F8ECE31FF6A" box="[617,804,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Brachyauchenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more akin to 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FC517F8FC88DFF6B" authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[986,1432,150,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Aemasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FC517F8FC92FFF6B" box="[986,1082,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Aemasia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBCB329FBC97F8FC88DFF6B" author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[1090,1432,150,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" refId="ref7271" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1895) Monographie der Pseudophylliden. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien. 45, 282 pp." type="book" year="1895">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the lateral lobes expanded to the sides in dorsal view, although 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FC157FA3CEEBFF0F" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[926,1022,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Aemasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FC157FA3CEEBFF0F" box="[926,1022,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Aemasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FB467FA2C88DFF0F" authority="Stal, 1875" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1875" box="[1229,1432,186,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Diyllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FB467FA2C80BFF0E" box="[1229,1310,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Diyllus</emphasis>
Stål, 1875
</taxonomicName>
. In the current featuring of the genus (only including 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FD577FC7CE7DFF22" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[732,872,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FD577FC7CE7DFF22" box="[732,872,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">B. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FCF47FC6C92FFF22" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[895,1082,222,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FCF47FC6C92FFF22" box="[895,1082,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Brachyauchenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FA837FC7C883FF22" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[1288,1430,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Triencentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FA837FC7C883FF22" box="[1288,1430,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Triencentrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the following characters differentiate both genera: 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FC887E1ACEABFEC6" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[771,958,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FC887E1ACEABFEC6" box="[771,958,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Brachyauchenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a reddish-brown or dark brown coloration (the only species included with the costal area of the tegmina with yellowish stripes outlined in black), in contrast, the 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FE8B7E53CCF3FEBE" box="[256,486,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Triencentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FE8B7E53CC9BFEBE" box="[256,398,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Triencentrus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are light brown or yellowish-brown. The spines on the ventral margin of the femora and the dorsal margin of the hind tibia are thicker and more conspicuous in 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FC7B7E76C9BEFE52" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[1008,1195,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FC7B7E76C9BEFE52" box="[1008,1195,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Brachyauchenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FA837E77C883FE52" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[1288,1430,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Triencentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FA837E77C883FE52" box="[1288,1430,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Triencentrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both genera have similar cerci structures (cylindrical and armed by a small inward spine at the apex), although some species of 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FED87EAFCCF4FE0A" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[339,481,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Triencentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FED87EAFCCF4FE0A" box="[339,481,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Triencentrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bifurcate close to the apex (
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FCAF7EAFCE46FE0A" box="[804,851,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">e.g.,</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FCD77EAFC9FCFE0B" authority="Beier, 1960" authorityName="Beier" authorityYear="1960" box="[860,1257,438,465]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Triencentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobatus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FCD77EAFC94FFE0A" box="[860,1114,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Triencentrus bilobatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBCB329FBE97EAEC9FCFE0B" author="Beier, M." box="[1122,1257,438,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" pagination="396" refId="ref7013" refString="Beier, M. (1960) Orthoptera Tettigoniidae (Pseudophyllinae II). In: Mertens, R., Hennig, W. &amp; Wermuth, H. (Eds.), Das Tierreich. 74, Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co., Berlin, pp. 396." type="book chapter" year="1960">Beier, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Regarding the subgenital plate of males, there are no modifications of the common shape. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FB0B7EC2C82EFE2E" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[1152,1339,474,500]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FB0B7EC2C82EFE2E" box="[1152,1339,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Brachyauchenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the styli are conspicuously long, as long as the subgenital plate. On the other hand, in 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FC707EE7C99CFDC2" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[1019,1161,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Triencentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FC707EE7C99CFDC2" box="[1019,1161,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Triencentrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the styli are half long or at most three-quarters of the subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="50C98CD9FFBCB329FF4C7D5ECF59FC86" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="186CDF52FFBCB329FF4C7D5ECF59FC86" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FF4C7D5ECC5AFDBA" bold="true" box="[199,335,582,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Comments.</emphasis>
The nominal species 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FDDA7D5FCFF7FDBA" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[593,738,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FDDA7D5FCFF7FDBA" box="[593,738,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">B. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
significantly differs morphologically from the other species currently included in the genus, making it necessary to allocate 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FCE47D73CEFDFD5E" authorityName="Nickle" authorityYear="2006" box="[879,1000,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FCE47D73CEFDFD5E" box="[879,1000,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">B. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FBAA7D73C996FD5E" authorityName="Griffini" authorityYear="1896" box="[1057,1155,618,644]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festae">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FBAA7D73C996FD5E" box="[1057,1155,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">B. festae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into a new genus and to move 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FF557D97CC7FFD72" authorityName="Piza" authorityYear="1980" box="[222,362,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicosus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FF557D97CC7FFD72" box="[222,362,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">B. varicosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FE197D96CE04FD73" authority="Redtenbacher, 1895" authorityName="Redtenbacher" authorityYear="1895" box="[402,785,654,681]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Stenoschema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FE197D96CF31FD72" box="[402,548,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Stenoschema</emphasis>
Redtenbacher, 1895
</taxonomicName>
. With these nomenclatural acts, 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FB0E7D96C827FD72" box="[1157,1330,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Brachyachenus</emphasis>
becomes monotypic. It was necessary to provide a new diagnosis for the genus once the diagnoses proposed in the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBCB329FEA87DCECF6EFD2B" author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[291,635,726,753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" refId="ref7271" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1895) Monographie der Pseudophylliden. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien. 45, 282 pp." type="book" year="1895">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895</bibRefCitation>
) and by 
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBCB329FD6B7DCECE65FD2B" author="Beier, M." box="[736,880,726,753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" pagination="396" refId="ref7013" refString="Beier, M. (1960) Orthoptera Tettigoniidae (Pseudophyllinae II). In: Mertens, R., Hennig, W. &amp; Wermuth, H. (Eds.), Das Tierreich. 74, Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co., Berlin, pp. 396." type="book chapter" year="1960">Beier (1960)</bibRefCitation>
were adjusted to the species allocated within the genus at each moment. Previously, the characters were general and could coincide with species of 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FA837DE3C883FCCE" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[1288,1430,763,788]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Triencentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FA837DE3C883FCCE" box="[1288,1430,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Triencentrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FF1C7C06CC2EFCE2" box="[151,315,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FF1C7C06CC22FCE2" authorityName="Beier" authorityYear="1960" box="[151,311,798,824]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Xiphophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xiphophyllum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FEFB7C06CF85FCE2" authority="Beier, 1962" authorityName="Beier" authorityYear="1962" box="[368,656,798,824]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Baliophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FEFB7C06CF12FCE2" box="[368,519,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Baliophyllum</emphasis>
Beier, 1962
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBCB329FC867C06CEDDFCE2" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[781,968,798,824]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Brachyauchenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBCB329FC867C06CEDDFCE2" box="[781,968,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="549">Brachyauchenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from these two last genera by the brachypterous condition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
